Posts.Content: Jojo0529 wrote: Hi ladies, I am doing well, with the exception of the voice in my head that tells me I should not be. I wonder if I am truly an anomaly, or if anyone else has a similar situation. I had a large tumor (2.5cm) that lay in my breast for years ( either misdiagnosed as b9, or turned cancerous). I am so sick of hearing about early detection. Money and resources need to go toward preventing, or healing recurrence/mets. Anyway, my lymph nodes were negative. I am er/pr strongly positive. Onco 17, Miotic rate of 1, scary ki-67 of 25. grade 2/3. I am thrilled with the negative nodes, but I obsess over how it could sit and not spread, when some women have a tumor for a few months that spreads. Has anyone else had a tumor for a long time?
